00:38:41.930 --> 00:38:44.340 align:middle line:84%
naive about this
entire situation.

00:38:44.340 --> 00:38:46.060 align:middle line:84%
I mean, for the
first couple days,

00:38:46.060 --> 00:38:48.380 align:middle line:84%
I think it's easy for
all of us to prepare.

00:38:48.380 --> 00:38:51.270 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've talked about it on
"Coast to Coast," where you get

00:38:51.270 --> 00:38:52.990 align:middle line:90%
some food for a couple weeks.

00:38:52.990 --> 00:38:54.890 align:middle line:90%
You get enough water put away.

00:38:54.890 --> 00:38:57.440 align:middle line:84%
And that's good
for the short term.

00:38:57.440 --> 00:39:00.290 align:middle line:10%
But what are we going to
do about the long term

00:39:00.290 --> 00:39:04.560 align:middle line:10%
if the power grid is gone
for a year or two years?

00:39:04.560 --> 00:39:07.110 align:middle line:84%
They don't have enough
transformers, for example,

00:39:07.110 --> 00:39:08.960 align:middle line:90%
to bring into the country.

00:39:08.960 --> 00:39:11.680 align:middle line:84%
What do we do if
it gets that long?

00:39:11.680 --> 00:39:13.470 align:middle line:84%
Honestly, we're up
a creek, aren't we?

00:39:13.470 --> 00:39:14.820 align:middle line:90%
>>AKART: Most people will be.

00:39:14.820 --> 00:39:17.520 align:middle line:84%
And so you have to
plan ahead and think

00:39:17.520 --> 00:39:20.020 align:middle line:90%
about, where will I go?

00:39:20.020 --> 00:39:23.810 align:middle line:84%
Now, a lot of folks might think
they can just head out I-70 out

00:39:23.810 --> 00:39:27.077 align:middle line:84%
into the country or, in
my neck of the woods, go

00:39:27.077 --> 00:39:28.410 align:middle line:90%
and the farmers will take me in.

00:39:28.410 --> 00:39:28.870 align:middle line:90%
They won't.

00:39:28.870 --> 00:39:30.661 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You think we
have traffic jams now

00:39:30.661 --> 00:39:31.570 align:middle line:90%
in Los Angeles?

00:39:31.570 --> 00:39:32.040 align:middle line:90%
>>AKART: Exactly.

00:39:32.040 --> 00:39:33.100 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wait till this happens.

00:39:33.100 --> 00:39:34.350 align:middle line:90%
>>AKART: That's exactly right.

00:39:34.350 --> 00:39:38.460 align:middle line:84%
And the thing about--
what will be interesting,

00:39:38.460 --> 00:39:41.200 align:middle line:84%
you'll have small communities
that will band together.

00:39:41.200 --> 00:39:43.060 align:middle line:84%
And then they'll
close their borders.

00:39:43.060 --> 00:39:45.840 align:middle line:84%
And when the golden hordes,
as they're referred to,

00:39:45.840 --> 00:39:48.460 align:middle line:84%
come out of the city
looking for food and water,

00:39:48.460 --> 00:39:50.160 align:middle line:84%
they'll find that
they're not welcome,

00:39:50.160 --> 00:39:52.364 align:middle line:84%
because people will
take care of their own.

00:39:52.364 --> 00:39:53.780 align:middle line:84%
Those who think
they're just going

00:39:53.780 --> 00:39:56.120 align:middle line:84%
to go out and start a
garden and feed themselves

00:39:56.120 --> 00:39:58.320 align:middle line:90%
are very naive, as you say.

00:39:58.320 --> 00:40:00.740 align:middle line:84%
First off, they probably
have never tried to grow food

00:40:00.740 --> 00:40:01.950 align:middle line:84%
and wouldn't have
the first clue--

00:40:01.950 --> 00:40:03.760 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, and it
takes time to grow food.

00:40:03.760 --> 00:40:04.450 align:middle line:90%
>>AKART: It takes time.

00:40:04.450 --> 00:40:05.250 align:middle line:90%
It takes seeds.

00:40:05.250 --> 00:40:06.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You gotta eat tomorrow.

00:40:06.590 --> 00:40:09.950 align:middle line:10%
It's going to take you three
months to grow some tomatoes.

00:40:09.950 --> 00:40:12.580 align:middle line:10%
And that's not going to last
you too long, especially

00:40:12.580 --> 00:40:14.390 align:middle line:10%
if your neighbor steals them.

00:40:14.390 --> 00:40:15.700 align:middle line:90%
>>AKART: That's right.

00:40:15.700 --> 00:40:19.540 align:middle line:84%
The process of prepping
is three steps.

00:40:19.540 --> 00:40:22.560 align:middle line:90%
Number one, protect yourself.

00:40:22.560 --> 00:40:27.660 align:middle line:84%
Number two, have sufficient food
and water and medical supplies

00:40:27.660 --> 00:40:31.620 align:middle line:84%
to last until you can start
growing and harvesting

00:40:31.620 --> 00:40:33.450 align:middle line:90%
and canning your own food.

00:40:33.450 --> 00:40:36.520 align:middle line:84%
And then to have
long-term food storage

00:40:36.520 --> 00:40:39.500 align:middle line:84%
to supplement what you
won't be able to take

00:40:39.500 --> 00:40:40.960 align:middle line:90%
in now as nutrients.

00:40:40.960 --> 00:40:44.120 align:middle line:84%
And it could be simple like
beans and rice and pastas,

00:40:44.120 --> 00:40:44.920 align:middle line:90%
et cetera.

00:40:44.920 --> 00:40:49.410 align:middle line:84%
But you want to be able
to have a short-term plan,

00:40:49.410 --> 00:40:51.800 align:middle line:84%
a mid-term plan, and
a long-term plan.

00:40:51.800 --> 00:40:54.850 align:middle line:84%
And it's really not that
involved and that expensive.

00:40:54.850 --> 00:40:57.430 align:middle line:84%
It's just a matter of
deciding it's important.

00:40:57.430 --> 00:40:59.969 align:middle line:84%
And people can undertake
that process very easily.

00:40:59.969 --> 00:41:01.760 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now, if the
power system goes down

00:41:01.760 --> 00:41:04.880 align:middle line:84%
in the dead of winter when
it's 5 degrees above zero,

00:41:04.880 --> 00:41:06.020 align:middle line:90%
what do you do there?

00:41:06.020 --> 00:41:07.566 align:middle line:90%
You're out of luck.

00:41:07.566 --> 00:41:08.690 align:middle line:90%
How do you heat your house?

00:41:08.690 --> 00:41:10.650 align:middle line:90%
Your pipes begin to break.

00:41:10.650 --> 00:41:12.060 align:middle line:90%
Everything falls apart.

00:41:12.060 --> 00:41:14.330 align:middle line:84%
>>AKART: You have to have
alternative heating sources.

00:41:14.330 --> 00:41:18.770 align:middle line:84%
And this is where I'd suggest
to people, if you can,

00:41:18.770 --> 00:41:21.930 align:middle line:84%
consider reducing your
lifestyle and moving

00:41:21.930 --> 00:41:24.421 align:middle line:90%
to an area that's more rural.

00:41:24.421 --> 00:41:26.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How many
people can do that, Bob?

00:41:26.170 --> 00:41:28.200 align:middle line:84%
>>AKART: They can if
they're committed.

00:41:28.200 --> 00:41:31.050 align:middle line:84%
Now, I understand that you may
have a fabulous job working

00:41:31.050 --> 00:41:33.090 align:middle line:90%
for the bank in downtown LA.

00:41:33.090 --> 00:41:35.020 align:middle line:84%
But what you might
consider doing

00:41:35.020 --> 00:41:39.010 align:middle line:84%
is moving out into an
area and take a lesser pay

00:41:39.010 --> 00:41:42.400 align:middle line:84%
and maybe sell one of your cars
and move into a smaller home.

00:41:42.400 --> 00:41:45.430 align:middle line:84%
It's just a matter
of how important

00:41:45.430 --> 00:41:48.740 align:middle line:84%
is it to you to be prepared
for an event like this.

00:41:48.740 --> 00:41:50.180 align:middle line:84%
And not everybody
is willing to do

00:41:50.180 --> 00:41:52.540 align:middle line:84%
that, which is why the
EMP Commission said

00:41:52.540 --> 00:41:54.220 align:middle line:90%
90% will not survive.

00:41:54.220 --> 00:41:57.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The biggest
problem, I think,

00:41:57.030 --> 00:42:00.240 align:middle line:84%
it is that people don't
believe it could happen.

00:42:00.240 --> 00:42:01.310 align:middle line:90%
>>AKART: Yes.

00:42:01.310 --> 00:42:02.960 align:middle line:90%
The threat is real.

00:42:02.960 --> 00:42:04.290 align:middle line:10%
That's why I wrote the books.

00:42:04.290 --> 00:42:07.580 align:middle line:10%
Because the books
tell in great detail

00:42:07.580 --> 00:42:12.160 align:middle line:10%
not only the history behind
cyber warfare and EMP,

00:42:12.160 --> 00:42:14.870 align:middle line:10%
but then also the
real-life instances

00:42:14.870 --> 00:42:17.610 align:middle line:10%
of how these things
have been used.

00:42:17.610 --> 00:42:19.610 align:middle line:84%
But then the most
important part, I believe,

00:42:19.610 --> 00:42:23.700 align:middle line:84%
is where I tell people the
very realistic, simple steps

00:42:23.700 --> 00:42:25.250 align:middle line:84%
that you can take
to get prepared.

00:42:25.250 --> 00:42:26.380 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Well, that's good.

00:42:26.380 --> 00:42:29.100 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to be the
presenter of doom and gloom,

00:42:29.100 --> 00:42:32.330 align:middle line:84%
but, folks, if the
grid goes down,

00:42:32.330 --> 00:42:35.360 align:middle line:84%
we are in serious,
serious trouble.

00:42:35.360 --> 00:42:39.270 align:middle line:10%
I advise you all to write your
congressperson, your senator,

00:42:39.270 --> 00:42:42.770 align:middle line:10%
and demand that we
pass legislation

00:42:42.770 --> 00:42:47.000 align:middle line:10%
to insulate our power grid
from a solar flare, a cyber

00:42:47.000 --> 00:42:48.970 align:middle line:10%
attack, or an EMP.

00:42:48.970 --> 00:42:50.720 align:middle line:84%
Bob, thanks for being
on "Beyond Belief."

00:42:50.720 --> 00:42:51.845 align:middle line:90%
>>AKART: Thank you, George.

00:42:51.845 --> 00:42:53.100 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Let's get it done.

00:42:53.100 --> 00:42:53.900 align:middle line:90%
>>AKART: Yes.

00:42:53.900 --> 00:42:57.650 align:middle line:90%
